425. Mr. Speaker, Parliament completed the construction of the Office Complex for the 
Parliamentary Training Institute and the rehabilitation of the Eastern End Fence Wall 
Project. The conversion of the 2nd floor of the Chamber Block of Parliament into a 
Museum of Parliament was completed and inaugurated by the Rt. Hon. Speaker A.S.K 
Bagbin. The Museum was set up to preserve and tell the history of Parliament from 
the precolonial days to the republics, thereafter, aimed at preserving the Legislative 
History of G hana. In 2025, Parliament will continue to discharge all constitutional 
obligations, including ongoing projects and programmes. 
